Nigerian Export Promotion Council (NEPC) has tasked Nigerian prospective exporters on packaging for international markets in Kaduna State. The council urged the Nigerian exporters to explore and sell their products in the global markets. Speaking at a day Workshop on “Positioning Nigeria Products in Certified Niche Markets in the USA, EU, UK, etc, NEPC ‘s Executive Director, Dr Ezra Yakusak, said  26 Small and Medium Enterprises (SMEs)’ exporters were presented with certifications by the council after sponsoring and supporting them in 2021. Represented by Angela Uche-Echieh, the Chief Trade Promotion Officer explained further that the council has also concluded pre-audit of the second batch of SME’s under this certification project.